        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): treat generic 'LLM request failed' error as transient server_error",
        "body": "Closes #93931\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe generic assistant error text `\"LLM request failed.\"` was not classified as any transient error type — `classifyFailoverReason` returned `null`, so `resolveCronExecutionRetryHint` returned `{ retryable: false }` and `payload.fallbacks` never engaged.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe exact-match regex `/^llm request failed\\\\.$/i` classifies this error as `server_error` (transient), enabling cron retry and model fallback. Only the bare `\"LLM request failed.\"` string matches; variants like `\"LLM request failed: provider rejected the request schema or tool payload.\"` are not caught (they are format errors, not transient).\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { classifyFailoverReason } from \"./src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/errors.ts\"; ...'\n\nclassifyFailoverReason results:\nLLM request failed.                                   → server_error\nllm request failed.                                   → server_error\nLLM request failed: provider rejected the schema...   → null\nLLM request failed: connection refused...              → null\n```\n\n**Not tested:** Live gateway cron job execution with an actual LM Studio model-not-loaded failure.",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93931-model-fallbacks-never-engage",
